<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en-AU">
<head>
<meta charset="utf-8">
<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1">
<title>Communiti — Hear every issue in every voice</title>
<meta name="description" content="Communiti now reads every piece of community feedback the way an analyst does: every issue, its own sentiment, the resident's exact words — in 10 community languages.">
<style>
  :root{
    --paper:#faf7f1;
    --paper-deep:#f3eee3;
    --ink:#1b2a3a;
    --ink-soft:#46586c;
    --teal:#0e7569;
    --teal-deep:#0a5249;
    --pos:#1a7f4e;
    --pos-soft:#dcf2e5;
    --neg:#b3372f;
    --neg-soft:#fae3df;
    --gold:#c9972b;
    --rule:#d8d0bf;
    --card:#ffffff;
    --serif:"Iowan Old Style","Palatino Linotype",Palatino,Georgia,"Times New Roman",serif;
    --sans:Seravek,"Gill Sans Nova","Avenir Next",Avenir,"Segoe UI",Frutiger,Calibri,sans-serif;
  }
  *{margin:0;padding:0;box-sizing:border-box}
  html{scroll-behavior:smooth}
  body{
    background:var(--paper);
    color:var(--ink);
    font-family:var(--sans);
    font-size:17px;
    line-height:1.65;
    background-image:
      radial-gradient(1200px 500px at 85% -5%, rgba(14,117,105,.07), transparent 60%),
      radial-gradient(900px 420px at -10% 30%, rgba(201,151,43,.06), transparent 55%);
  }
  .wrap{max-width:1060px;margin:0 auto;padding:0 28px}
  ::selection{background:var(--teal);color:#fff}

  /* ---------- reveal animation ---------- */
  @media (prefers-reduced-motion: no-preference){
    .reveal{opacity:0;transform:translateY(18px);animation:rise .8s cubic-bezier(.2,.7,.2,1) forwards}
    .reveal.d1{animation-delay:.12s}.reveal.d2{animation-delay:.24s}.reveal.d3{animation-delay:.38s}.reveal.d4{animation-delay:.52s}
    @keyframes rise{to{opacity:1;transform:none}}
    .bar-grow rect.metric{transform:scaleX(0);transform-origin:left;animation:grow 1.1s .5s cubic-bezier(.2,.7,.2,1) forwards}
    @keyframes grow{to{transform:scaleX(1)}}
  }

  /* ---------- masthead ---------- */
  header.masthead{
    border-bottom:1px solid var(--rule);
    padding:22px 0;
    display:flex;align-items:center;justify-content:space-between;
  }
  .brand{font-family:var(--serif);font-weight:700;font-size:24px;letter-spacing:.01em}
  .brand em{color:var(--teal);font-style:normal}
  .masthead-note{font-size:13px;color:var(--ink-soft);letter-spacing:.14em;text-transform:uppercase}

  /* ---------- hero ---------- */
  .hero{padding:84px 0 30px}
  .kicker{
    display:inline-block;background:var(--ink);color:var(--paper);
    font-size:12.5px;letter-spacing:.18em;text-transform:uppercase;
    padding:7px 14px;border-radius:3px;margin-bottom:28px;
  }
  h1{
    font-family:var(--serif);font-weight:700;
    font-size:clamp(40px,6.4vw,68px);
    line-height:1.06;letter-spacing:-.015em;max-width:17ch;
  }
  h1 .accent{color:var(--teal)}
  .lede{
    margin-top:26px;max-width:62ch;font-size:21px;line-height:1.55;color:var(--ink-soft);
  }
  .lede strong{color:var(--ink)}

  /* ---------- the example card ---------- */
  .example{
    margin:56px 0 0;
    background:var(--card);
    border:1px solid var(--rule);
    border-radius:14px;
    box-shadow:0 24px 60px -36px rgba(27,42,58,.35);
    overflow:hidden;
  }
  .example-head{
    padding:14px 24px;border-bottom:1px solid var(--rule);
    display:flex;justify-content:space-between;align-items:center;gap:12px;flex-wrap:wrap;
    background:var(--paper-deep);
    font-size:13px;letter-spacing:.08em;text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--ink-soft);
  }
  .example-body{padding:34px 36px 8px;font-family:var(--serif);font-size:clamp(22px,3vw,30px);line-height:1.6}
  mark{padding:.08em .18em;border-radius:4px;font-style:normal}
  mark.pos{background:var(--pos-soft);box-shadow:inset 0 -2px 0 var(--pos)}
  mark.neg{background:var(--neg-soft);box-shadow:inset 0 -2px 0 var(--neg)}
  .example-read{
    display:flex;gap:14px;flex-wrap:wrap;padding:22px 36px 30px;
  }
  .chip{
    display:inline-flex;align-items:center;gap:9px;
    font-size:14.5px;padding:8px 15px;border-radius:99px;border:1px solid var(--rule);background:#fff;
  }
  .dot{width:9px;height:9px;border-radius:50%}
  .dot.pos{background:var(--pos)}.dot.neg{background:var(--neg)}
  .chip b{font-weight:600}
  .chip span.topic{color:var(--ink-soft)}
  .example-foot{
    border-top:1px dashed var(--rule);padding:16px 36px 20px;font-size:15px;color:var(--ink-soft);
  }
  .example-foot b{color:var(--neg)}

  /* ---------- section scaffolding ---------- */
  section{padding:74px 0 10px}
  .eyebrow{
    font-size:13px;letter-spacing:.2em;text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--teal-deep);
    font-weight:600;margin-bottom:14px;
  }
  h2{
    font-family:var(--serif);font-weight:700;font-size:clamp(28px,4vw,42px);
    line-height:1.15;letter-spacing:-.01em;max-width:24ch;
  }
  .section-lede{margin-top:16px;max-width:64ch;color:var(--ink-soft);font-size:18px}

  /* ---------- stat band ---------- */
  .stats{
    margin-top:44px;
    display:grid;grid-template-columns:repeat(auto-fit,minmax(160px,1fr));
    border-top:2px solid var(--ink);
  }
  .stat{padding:24px 18px 28px;border-bottom:1px solid var(--rule)}
  .stat + .stat{border-left:1px solid var(--rule)}
  .stat .num{font-family:var(--serif);font-size:42px;font-weight:700;line-height:1;color:var(--ink)}
  .stat .num sup{font-size:18px;color:var(--gold);font-family:var(--sans)}
  .stat .lbl{margin-top:10px;font-size:14px;color:var(--ink-soft);line-height:1.45}

  /* ---------- charts ---------- */
  figure.chart{
    margin-top:42px;background:var(--card);border:1px solid var(--rule);border-radius:14px;
    padding:30px 30px 22px;box-shadow:0 18px 48px -38px rgba(27,42,58,.4);
  }
  figure.chart figcaption{
    font-size:14px;color:var(--ink-soft);margin-top:14px;padding-top:14px;border-top:1px dashed var(--rule);
  }
  figure.chart figcaption b{color:var(--ink)}
  .chart-title{font-family:var(--serif);font-size:22px;font-weight:700;margin-bottom:4px}
  .chart-sub{font-size:14.5px;color:var(--ink-soft);margin-bottom:18px}
  svg{display:block;width:100%;height:auto}
  svg text{font-family:var(--sans)}

  .two-col{display:grid;grid-template-columns:1fr 1fr;gap:26px}
  @media(max-width:840px){.two-col{grid-template-columns:1fr}}

  /* ---------- language grid ---------- */
  .langs{margin-top:36px;display:grid;grid-template-columns:repeat(auto-fit,minmax(190px,1fr));gap:12px}
  .lang{
    background:var(--card);border:1px solid var(--rule);border-radius:10px;padding:14px 16px;
    display:flex;justify-content:space-between;align-items:center;gap:10px;
  }
  .lang .name{font-weight:600;font-size:15.5px}
  .lang .native{display:block;font-size:13px;color:var(--ink-soft);font-weight:400}
  .tick{color:var(--pos);font-size:18px;font-weight:700}
  .lang-note{margin-top:16px;font-size:14.5px;color:var(--ink-soft)}
  .lang-note b{color:var(--neg)}

  /* ---------- story callout ---------- */
  .callout{
    margin-top:48px;border-radius:16px;overflow:hidden;
    background:var(--ink);color:#eef2ee;
    background-image:radial-gradient(700px 320px at 90% -20%, rgba(14,117,105,.5), transparent 60%);
  }
  .callout-inner{padding:52px 48px}
  .callout .eyebrow{color:var(--gold)}
  .callout h3{font-family:var(--serif);font-size:clamp(26px,3.6vw,38px);font-weight:700;line-height:1.18;max-width:24ch}
  .callout p{margin-top:18px;max-width:62ch;color:#c3cfd4;font-size:17.5px}
  .callout .big{
    font-family:var(--serif);font-size:clamp(54px,9vw,96px);font-weight:700;color:#fff;line-height:1;
    margin:26px 0 6px;
  }
  .callout .big small{font-size:.35em;color:var(--gold);font-family:var(--sans);font-weight:600;letter-spacing:.06em}

  /* ---------- steps ---------- */
  .steps{margin-top:40px;display:grid;grid-template-columns:repeat(auto-fit,minmax(240px,1fr));gap:22px}
  .step{background:var(--card);border:1px solid var(--rule);border-radius:12px;padding:26px}
  .step .n{
    font-family:var(--serif);font-size:15px;font-weight:700;color:var(--paper);
    background:var(--teal);width:30px;height:30px;border-radius:50%;
    display:flex;align-items:center;justify-content:center;margin-bottom:16px;
  }
  .step h4{font-size:17px;margin-bottom:8px}
  .step p{font-size:15px;color:var(--ink-soft)}

  /* ---------- IT section ---------- */
  .it-grid{margin-top:36px;display:grid;grid-template-columns:repeat(auto-fit,minmax(250px,1fr));gap:22px}
  .it-card{border-left:3px solid var(--teal);padding:4px 0 4px 20px}
  .it-card h4{font-size:16.5px;margin-bottom:6px}
  .it-card p{font-size:15px;color:var(--ink-soft)}

  /* ---------- footnotes ---------- */
  .notes{margin-top:70px;border-top:2px solid var(--ink);padding-top:26px}
  .notes h3{font-family:var(--serif);font-size:20px;margin-bottom:14px}
  .notes ol{padding-left:20px;max-width:78ch}
  .notes li{font-size:14px;color:var(--ink-soft);margin-bottom:10px;line-height:1.6}

  /* ---------- CTA / footer ---------- */
  .cta{
    margin:80px 0 0;text-align:center;padding:70px 28px 78px;
    border-top:1px solid var(--rule);
    background:linear-gradient(180deg, transparent, rgba(14,117,105,.06));
  }
  .cta h2{margin:0 auto;max-width:22ch}
  .cta p{margin:18px auto 0;max-width:52ch;color:var(--ink-soft)}
  .btn{
    display:inline-block;margin-top:30px;background:var(--teal);color:#fff;text-decoration:none;
    font-weight:600;font-size:17px;padding:16px 34px;border-radius:8px;
    box-shadow:0 14px 30px -14px rgba(14,117,105,.65);
    transition:transform .15s ease, box-shadow .15s ease;
  }
  .btn:hover{transform:translateY(-2px);box-shadow:0 20px 36px -14px rgba(14,117,105,.7)}
  .btn.ghost{background:transparent;color:var(--teal-deep);border:1.5px solid var(--teal);box-shadow:none;margin-left:14px}
  footer{padding:34px 0 50px;font-size:13.5px;color:var(--ink-soft);display:flex;justify-content:space-between;gap:16px;flex-wrap:wrap;border-top:1px solid var(--rule);margin-top:0}
</style>
</head>
<body>

<div class="wrap">
  <header class="masthead">
    <div class="brand">communiti<em>.</em></div>
    <div class="masthead-note">Product update · June 2026</div>
  </header>

  <!-- ================= HERO ================= -->
  <section class="hero" style="padding-top:64px">
    <span class="kicker reveal">New · Issue-level sentiment analysis</span>
    <h1 class="reveal d1">Your community tells you everything.<br><span class="accent">Now you can hear all of it.</span></h1>
    <p class="lede reveal d2">
      Until now, feedback tools gave each response <strong>one</strong> sentiment score — and called
      anything complicated <strong>“mixed.”</strong> Communiti now reads every submission the way your best
      analyst does: <strong>every issue, its own sentiment, the resident’s exact words</strong> — filed
      straight into your dashboard topics, in ten community languages.
    </p>

    <div class="example reveal d3" aria-label="Worked example of issue-level analysis">
      <div class="example-head">
        <span>One real-style response</span>
        <span>What Communiti reads</span>
      </div>
      <div class="example-body">
        “I really <mark class="pos">love the train service</mark>, but I
        <mark class="neg">hate how terrible the bus delays are getting</mark>!”
      </div>
      <div class="example-read">
        <span class="chip"><span class="dot pos"></span><b>Train service</b> · positive · <span class="topic">Trains &amp; Ferries</span></span>
        <span class="chip"><span class="dot neg"></span><b>Bus delays</b> · negative · <span class="topic">Buses</span></span>
      </div>
      <div class="example-foot">
        Every other tool we tested scores this whole response as <b>“MIXED”</b> — and the trains and the buses both disappear.
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ================= NUMBERS ================= -->
  <section>
    <p class="eyebrow reveal">Tested before we shipped it</p>
    <h2 class="reveal d1">Benchmarked on the messiest feedback we could write</h2>
    <p class="section-lede reveal d2">
      We built a 217-response test set designed to break sentiment tools — typos, sarcasm, rambling
      voice transcripts, low-literacy writing, and ten languages — then measured everything.
      The full method and results are published alongside this page.<sup>1</sup>
    </p>
    <div class="stats reveal d3">
      <div class="stat"><div class="num">92<sup>%</sup></div><div class="lbl">of issues found, even in deliberately messy feedback</div></div>
      <div class="stat"><div class="num">99<sup>%</sup></div><div class="lbl">sentiment accuracy on the issues it finds</div></div>
      <div class="stat"><div class="num">100<sup>%</sup></div><div class="lbl">of “mixed” responses split into their real issues</div></div>
      <div class="stat"><div class="num">10</div><div class="lbl">community languages read natively, including Te Reo Māori and Samoan</div></div>
      <div class="stat"><div class="num">~2<sup>s</sup></div><div class="lbl">per response, from about $3 per thousand responses</div></div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ================= VS COMPREHEND ================= -->
  <section>
    <p class="eyebrow reveal">Head to head № 1</p>
    <h2 class="reveal d1">The industry-standard tool misses what residents don’t name</h2>
    <p class="section-lede reveal d2">
      Most platforms (and many in-house projects) run on Amazon Comprehend — it tags <em>things</em> it can
      recognise. But residents rarely name things. They write
      <em>“Twenty minutes on hold just to ask why my rates notice changed.”</em> There is no “customer
      service” in that sentence — only the experience of it.
    </p>

    <div class="two-col">
      <figure class="chart reveal d2">
        <div class="chart-title">Issue detection score — long written submissions</div>
        <div class="chart-sub">60 multi-issue submissions · 700 issues to find · same scoring for both<sup>2</sup></div>
        <svg viewBox="0 0 520 150" role="img" aria-label="Bar chart: Communiti finds 100 percent of issues, Amazon Comprehend 33 percent" class="bar-grow">
          <text x="0" y="22" font-size="15" font-weight="600" fill="#1b2a3a">Communiti</text>
          <rect x="0" y="32" width="500" height="30" rx="5" fill="#f3eee3"/>
          <rect class="metric" x="0" y="32" width="500" height="30" rx="5" fill="#0e7569"/>
          <text x="490" y="53" font-size="16" font-weight="700" fill="#ffffff" text-anchor="end">100%</text>
          <text x="0" y="98" font-size="15" font-weight="600" fill="#1b2a3a">Amazon Comprehend (best setting)</text>
          <rect x="0" y="108" width="500" height="30" rx="5" fill="#f3eee3"/>
          <rect class="metric" x="0" y="108" width="165" height="30" rx="5" fill="#c9972b"/>
          <text x="175" y="129" font-size="16" font-weight="700" fill="#1b2a3a">33%</text>
        </svg>
        <figcaption>Comprehend left <b>233 significant issues</b> unreported across those 60 submissions. Communiti left none.</figcaption>
      </figure>

      <figure class="chart reveal d3">
        <div class="chart-title">Issue detection score — issues implied, never named</div>
        <div class="chart-sub">96 responses like “water comes over the kerb every time it rains”<sup>2</sup></div>
        <svg viewBox="0 0 520 150" role="img" aria-label="Bar chart: Communiti finds 90 percent of implied issues, Amazon Comprehend 1 percent" class="bar-grow">
          <text x="0" y="22" font-size="15" font-weight="600" fill="#1b2a3a">Communiti</text>
          <rect x="0" y="32" width="500" height="30" rx="5" fill="#f3eee3"/>
          <rect class="metric" x="0" y="32" width="450" height="30" rx="5" fill="#0e7569"/>
          <text x="440" y="53" font-size="16" font-weight="700" fill="#ffffff" text-anchor="end">90%</text>
          <text x="0" y="98" font-size="15" font-weight="600" fill="#1b2a3a">Amazon Comprehend (best setting)</text>
          <rect x="0" y="108" width="500" height="30" rx="5" fill="#f3eee3"/>
          <rect class="metric" x="0" y="108" width="7" height="30" rx="3" fill="#c9972b"/>
          <text x="17" y="129" font-size="16" font-weight="700" fill="#1b2a3a">1%</text>
        </svg>
        <figcaption>This is most of what consultation feedback looks like — and it is <b>structurally invisible</b> to entity-tagging tools.</figcaption>
      </figure>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ================= LANGUAGES ================= -->
  <section>
    <p class="eyebrow reveal">Head to head № 2</p>
    <h2 class="reveal d1">Feedback in ten community languages — read, not skipped</h2>
    <p class="section-lede reveal d2">
      Residents write the way they speak — sometimes switching language mid-sentence:
      <em>“公交车总是晚点, but the new library hours are very helpful.”</em>
      Communiti reads the complaint about buses <em>and</em> the praise for the library.
      Comprehend’s issue-level analysis supports English only.
    </p>
    <div class="langs reveal d3">
      <div class="lang"><span class="name">Mandarin <span class="native">中文</span></span><span class="tick">✓</span></div>
      <div class="lang"><span class="name">Arabic <span class="native">العربية</span></span><span class="tick">✓</span></div>
      <div class="lang"><span class="name">Vietnamese <span class="native">Tiếng Việt</span></span><span class="tick">✓</span></div>
      <div class="lang"><span class="name">Cantonese <span class="native">廣東話</span></span><span class="tick">✓</span></div>
      <div class="lang"><span class="name">Punjabi <span class="native">ਪੰਜਾਬੀ</span></span><span class="tick">✓</span></div>
      <div class="lang"><span class="name">Greek <span class="native">Ελληνικά</span></span><span class="tick">✓</span></div>
      <div class="lang"><span class="name">Italian <span class="native">Italiano</span></span><span class="tick">✓</span></div>
      <div class="lang"><span class="name">Hindi <span class="native">हिन्दी</span></span><span class="tick">✓</span></div>
      <div class="lang"><span class="name">Te Reo Māori</span><span class="tick">✓</span></div>
      <div class="lang"><span class="name">Samoan <span class="native">Gagana Sāmoa</span></span><span class="tick">✓</span></div>
    </div>
    <p class="lang-note reveal d4">Industry-standard issue-level analysis: <b>0 of 10</b> supported.</p>
  </section>

  <!-- ================= VS DIY AI ================= -->
  <section>
    <p class="eyebrow reveal">Head to head № 3</p>
    <h2 class="reveal d1">“Couldn’t we just paste it into an AI assistant?”</h2>
    <p class="section-lede reveal d2">
      Fair question — we tested it properly, including with the <em>same AI model we use ourselves</em>.
      Today’s AI assistants read well. The difference is what arrives at the other end: a consultation
      dashboard needs every issue filed under <em>your</em> topics, with the resident’s words attached,
      for every row in the spreadsheet — every time.
    </p>

    <figure class="chart reveal d2">
      <div class="chart-title">Share of issues that arrive in your dashboard, correctly filed</div>
      <div class="chart-sub">60 long submissions · found <em>and</em> filed under the right reporting topic<sup>3</sup></div>
      <svg viewBox="0 0 520 226" role="img" aria-label="Bar chart: Communiti 93 percent, AI assistant one response at a time 5 percent, AI assistant whole spreadsheet 0 percent" class="bar-grow">
        <text x="0" y="22" font-size="15" font-weight="600" fill="#1b2a3a">Communiti</text>
        <rect x="0" y="32" width="500" height="30" rx="5" fill="#f3eee3"/>
        <rect class="metric" x="0" y="32" width="465" height="30" rx="5" fill="#0e7569"/>
        <text x="455" y="53" font-size="16" font-weight="700" fill="#ffffff" text-anchor="end">93%</text>

        <text x="0" y="98" font-size="15" font-weight="600" fill="#1b2a3a">AI assistant — one response at a time, carefully prompted</text>
        <rect x="0" y="108" width="500" height="30" rx="5" fill="#f3eee3"/>
        <rect class="metric" x="0" y="108" width="25" height="30" rx="4" fill="#7c5cb8"/>
        <text x="35" y="129" font-size="16" font-weight="700" fill="#1b2a3a">5%</text>

        <text x="0" y="174" font-size="15" font-weight="600" fill="#1b2a3a">AI assistant — whole spreadsheet pasted in at once</text>
        <rect x="0" y="184" width="500" height="30" rx="5" fill="#f3eee3"/>
        <rect class="metric" x="0" y="184" width="4" height="30" rx="2" fill="#b3372f"/>
        <text x="14" y="205" font-size="16" font-weight="700" fill="#b3372f">0%</text>
      </svg>
      <figcaption>
        The assistant finds issues, then names its themes differently on every row — so almost nothing
        lands in your reporting structure without someone re-filing it by hand. <b>That re-filing is the job Communiti does.</b>
      </figcaption>
    </figure>

    <div class="callout reveal d3">
      <div class="callout-inner">
        <p class="eyebrow">What happened with the spreadsheet</p>
        <h3>We pasted 60 real-length submissions into an AI assistant, twenty at a time.</h3>
        <div class="big">0 <small>OF 60 CAME BACK USABLE</small></div>
        <p>
          Every batch hit the assistant’s output limit and stopped mid-answer. No error message — just a
          response that quietly cut off. On short one-line comments the same trick worked fine; on real
          consultation submissions it returned nothing. That’s the risk: it doesn’t fail loudly, it
          <em>silently drops residents from your analysis</em>.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ================= HOW IT WORKS ================= -->
  <section>
    <p class="eyebrow reveal">How it works</p>
    <h2 class="reveal d1">Nothing new to learn</h2>
    <div class="steps reveal d2">
      <div class="step"><div class="n">1</div><h4>Upload as usual</h4><p>Spreadsheets, survey exports, documents, audio transcripts — exactly as you do today.</p></div>
      <div class="step"><div class="n">2</div><h4>Every issue surfaces</h4><p>Each response is read for every issue it raises, with its own sentiment and the resident’s exact words highlighted.</p></div>
      <div class="step"><div class="n">3</div><h4>Your dashboard fills itself</h4><p>Issues are filed under your project’s topics automatically — and you can rename or merge topics at any time.</p></div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ================= FOR IT ================= -->
  <section>
